Not surprised either. I'm old enough to remember it come out. Horribly buggy and poor launch, and Sierra is just some tiny little poor company. A computer to run Tribes was like 1500$.

Before FPs was just QUake and death death match .
author: magicalpoop

text:
Not even HALO3 can still compare to Tribes2.

64 players
Vehicle Combat
Jet packs (Adds the 3rd dimension to FPS)

In Halo its a matter of firing your rifle and holding down the fire button to melee someone with the claw or rifle butt.

In tribes, its about predicting if your disc-launcher will hit the guy..Rationing your jetpack to ski+move around the map..etc..

HALO3's gameplay is like childsplay still in comparision to TRIBES.
